President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the appointment of Mr Abdullahi Bala as the new Executive Secretary for the Nigeria Police Trust Fund (NPTF). A statement by Mr Osaigbovo Ehisienmen, the Press Secretary to the Minister of Police Affairs, on Tuesday in Abuja said Bala took over from Mr Ahmed Aliyu. Ehisienmen said Aliyu had resigned his appointment to run for gubernatorial primaries in compliance with the directives of the president. He said that the new Executive Secretary, born on  Aug. 18, 1967 in Sokoto North Local Government Area, holds a Masters Degree in Political Science from the Usmanu Danfodiyo University, Sokoto. “His work career began in 1992, when he was appointed as Personal Officer II, Admin and Political Affairs Department, Cabinet Office, Sokoto. “His career trajectory got to its apex in May, 2009, when he was appointed as Permanent Secretary in Sokoto State Civil Service. “The highly cerebral and resourceful administrator, worked as Permanent Secretary in several Ministries, Departments and Agencies in the state,” he said. Ehisienmen said the new Executive Secretary had also held several other appointments including Secretary to Sokoto State Government Committee on Audit Inspection Report. According to him, he has also served as the Chairman, Health Financing Technical Group and Secretary, Sokoto State Government Policy Council on the State of Emergency on Education. He said the appointment was with immediate effect. 